column10:
my favorite game that I Suck At

if you want more content and don't really care about graphics, the complete version is on gog (it's a gorgeous game either way imo... maybe i'm biased because i've been playing it since release)
i highly recommend getting both! (+HD mod for gog)

I am a big fan of HoMM games, my first introduction to this franchise was back in 2006 when Heroes of Might & Magic V was  released. I reeeeaaaally loved that game. My PC wasn't running it that well, loading were long and graphics low, but I was enjoying every second of it. And after getting to know the franchise, all these years I have been hearing about HoMM III, how it is the best, how it is superior, how it is perfect and all. Finally in 2015 I had a chance to get my hands, well, the cursor of my mouse to be precise xD, on the official version of HoMM III (till that time I haven't played it ever as I didn't want to play its pirate version, I have my code LOL). So, in 2021 I finally had time and courage to install this game. I played the campaign and multiplayer to give my objective opinion. In the end, I wanted to know what the hype around this game was about. And I am kind of disappointed. Not because "ugh, pixels! I hate pixels!1!!1!!". Well first, I should say that I grew up in 90's with pixel graphics of Civilization and Warcraft 2, so pixels aren't an issue here, but the story. It simply is medicore, yeah, even for this old game. Some things I want to clear:
- The game is complex, at least for new players. I admit, even I, a hardcore fan of HoMM franchise, had hard time in the beginning to differentiate objects and icons;
- About differentiating, there is slight or no gap among fractions, it is hard to recognize which town belong to which fraction. I don't mean it is that hard, but you know, in HoMM V you can get the idea of Inferno town just by looking at it, even if you are a total newbie and has no idea what the game is about, you will still get the idea it belongs to demons, got it? Also, heroes seem to have more human-ish look. It, honestly, bugged me.
- About creature designs. I wouldn't go that far to totally crush this game with my critical review as this game is old and it did a great job to portray creatures in a more enjoyable, aesthetic and charismatic way, HOWEVER, they could have done Devils better. Devils in black night dress with a scythe in their hands?! LMAO;
- Story. As I said it is just medicore. Don't start "shut up, you hater". Throw your nostalgia sh*t and look closely what you are playing. Again, I will give an example from HoMM V, not because I have nostalgia sh*t for that game, but it really deserves more attention and love than it gets. The story of HoMM V trilogy, in my honest opinion, is one of the best not only among HoMM franchise, but among in games I have played in general! I am serious. They could just create Netflix TV series based on it and I would watch it;
- Okay, after all this criticism you are probably thing why I gave thumbs up to this game, huh? The thing is that this game's gameplay, i.e playing mechanics is the same, the franchise never changes, and it is a good thing. Maybe the reason, that this game is still popular among TBS fans is because its gameplay mechanics? I don't deny, it is possible. I still am glad I bought and played this game. I enjoyed every second of it. It made me happy, too. But again, the story made me sad that it sucked, yeah, but the game is still HoMM, and I will always be happy to play any HoMM game.

The worst version of HoMM III that i have ever played. Two main reasons:
1. There is no option for random map, so you need to play only available scenarios;
2. The game crashes very offten;

- no random map;
- 4 slots for artifacts bag instead of 5;
- space dosen't work;
- citadel dosen't work => no damage from rivers/lava/etc => u can't defend the city  if u have a smaller army then the opponent => the walls are falling very fast => conclusion if u don't have almost an equal army in the city like youre opponent 90% of the times u will lose the city;
- works slow => u need to have a good PC/laptop configuration;
- I AM A REALLY OLD PLAYER OF HEROES M&M III, AND I ADORE THE GAME, BUT UNTILL ALL OF THE ABOVE ARE FIXED I certainly do not recomand the game.
